fields.Action:
Using the WebUI, create the following rule:
External IP address: IP address of the DUT
External port: port_ext
Protocol: TCP
Internel IP address: IP address of LAN_1
Internal port: port_1
Save the rule.
fields.Expected Result:
The DUT must not reboot in order to apply the rule.
Check that the rule is present in the data model, under:
InternetGatewayDevice.Layer3Forwarding.
Check that the iptables have been modified in order to take into account the rule.

fields.Action:
Using LAN_2, send the following traffic to the DUT:
IP destination address: WAN IP address of the DUT 
Protocol: TCP
Port: port_ext
fields.Expected Result: Check that LAN_1 receives the traffic on port_1.

fields.description:
Check if the DUT supports the Hairpinning behaviour.

	 


[Precondition]

	The DUT is on and connected to the Internet.

	2 LAN (or WLAN) PC are connected to the DUT: LAN_1 and LAN_2.

	One station on the WAN (WAN_1) is able to send traffic to the DUT.
